4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, Class 2 municipalities have
6 the authority to foreclose on properties for unpaid
7 municipal code violations after notice to interested
8 parties, including the property owner.
9 This bill would require Class 2 municipalities
10 to provide adjoining homeowners with notice of
11 foreclosure proceedings and to establish procedures
12 that allow adjoining homeowners to bid on the property
13 before the public auction.
14 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
15 technical revisions to update the existing code
16 language to current style.
17
18
19 A BILL
20 TO BE ENTITLED
21 AN ACT
22
23 Relating to Class 2 municipalities; to amend Section
24 11-40-62, as last amended by Act 2025-348, 2025 Regular
25 Session, and Section 11-40-69, Code of Alabama 1975; to
26 include adjoining homeowners as interested parties that must
27 receive notice of municipal lien foreclosures; to allow
28 adjoining homeowners to have bidding preference in
